stimulus:
In the next part today, we have a completely different short task.


This part involves keeping numbers in you mind. Participation takes around 5 minutes.

Welcome to the digit span task!


On each trial, you will see a sequence of digits, followed by a delay.


Then you will be asked to type them back in the same order in which they were seen.




For example, if you saw the digits 1, 2, 3, you would respond with 1, 2, 3




To ensure the best measure of true performance for our study,

it is very important that you do not use any memory aid (e.g., pen and paper).

Please do the task solely in your head.




There will be 12 total trials. Participation takes around 5 minutes.

What were the numbers in order?
(When you are ready to lock in your answer, press ENTER)
